cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with online handwritten text recognition, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques for analyzing pen-tip trajectories, natural language processing (NLP) techniques for recognizing Chinese characters, and machine learning (ML) techniques for training models. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach for incorporating lexicon constraints and prior knowledge about a certain language, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
